<body>
    <h1>Knowledge - Feature Specification</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Knowledge-FeatureSpecifica=
tion">Knowledge - Feature Specification</h1>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-TL;DR">TL;DR</h2>
<p>Knowledge introduces a manual, repository-scoped external-context layer =
for Bitloops.</p>
<p>The broader feature direction remains:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>ingest supported external records as stable <code>knowledge_items</code>=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>preserve immutable document versions</p></li>
<li>
<p>create explicit relations from knowledge to commits, checkpoints, artefa=
cts, and other knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>preserve old versions and old links without rewriting them</p></li>
<li>
<p>let later automations reuse the same low-level primitives</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The current implementation already delivers:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt; [--commit &lt;sha_or_ref&=
gt;]</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge associate &lt;source-ref&gt; --to &lt;tar=
get-ref&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge refresh &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;</code></p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge versions &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;</code></p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql query 'repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")-&gt;knowledge()'</=
code></p></li>
<li>
<p>supported source types:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub pull requests</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issues</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira issues</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence pages</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>repo-local provider config under <code>knowledge.providers</code></p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>shared Atlassian config under <code>knowledge.providers.atlassian</code>=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>current storage split:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>blob -&gt; full raw/content payload</p></li>
<li>
<p>DuckDB -&gt; document-version metadata and normalized/queryable fields</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>relational -&gt; source identities, knowledge items, and relation assert=
ions</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>version-aware source and target refs</p></li>
<li>
<p>latest-target-version resolution for unversioned knowledge targets</p></=
li>
</ul>
<p>This specification keeps the broader planned flows, but updates the impl=
emented slice to match the current codebase and test suite. Future work sta=
ys documented explicitly for structured discussion enrichment, richer retri=
eval/traversal, optional child ingestion, and later <code>historicalIntent(=
)</code> retrieval.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-1.Metadata">1. Metadata</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Feature name:</strong> Knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Module(s):</strong> CLI / <code>bitloops devql</code>, Query Eng=
ine / DevQL, Storage / relational + DuckDB + blob, Connectors / GitHub &amp=
; Atlassian</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Tech lead:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Status:</strong> Draft, implementation-aligned</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Priority:</strong> TBD</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Target release:</strong> Current MVP implemented slice + follow-=
up phases</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Linked Jira:</strong> CLI-1370, CLI-1371, CLI-1372, CLI-1373, CL=
I-1374, CLI-1375, CLI-1432</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Reference docs:</strong> <code>research.md</code>, <code>knowled=
ge-research.md</code>, <code>devql-knowledge-capability.md</code></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-2.Terminology">2. Terminology</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Knowledge item</strong> <br>
The stable identity of an ingested external record in the current repositor=
y scope.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Repository-scoped knowledge</strong> <br>
Knowledge that belongs to the current repository even if it is not linked t=
o a commit, checkpoint, artefact, or another knowledge item.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Document version</strong> <br>
An immutable snapshot of a knowledge item=E2=80=99s content and metadata.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Relation assertion</strong> <br>
An append-only record that links a source document version to a target such=
 as a commit, checkpoint, artefact, or another knowledge item.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Association method</strong> <br>
The mechanism by which a relation assertion entered the system, such as <co=
de>manual_attachment</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Canonical identity</strong> <br>
The provider-specific identity used to deduplicate a source into one stable=
 knowledge item.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Source ref</strong> <br>
A user-facing source identifier for <code>knowledge associate</code>, such =
as <code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;</code> or <code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt=
;:&lt;version_id&gt;</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Target ref</strong> <br>
A user-facing target identifier for <code>knowledge associate</code>, such =
as <code>commit:&lt;sha&gt;</code>, <code>checkpoint:&lt;id&gt;</code>, <co=
de>artefact:&lt;uuid&gt;</code>, or <code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;[:&lt;ve=
rsion_id&gt;]</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Discussion enrichment</strong> <br>
Future structured discussion content, such as PR reviews, issue comments, o=
r Confluence comments, stored separately from the canonical root body.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>Historical intent</strong> <br>
A later retrieval layer over the subset of knowledge that is linked to comm=
its and code history.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-3.Overview">3. Overview</h2>
<p>Bitloops already captures important in-repository signals:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>commits</p></li>
<li>
<p>checkpoint/session history</p></li>
<li>
<p>prompts</p></li>
<li>
<p>summaries</p></li>
<li>
<p>transcripts</p></li>
</ul>
<p>That foundation is useful, but it does not cover a large part of the rat=
ionale around a codebase. Important context often exists outside the reposi=
tory:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub pull requests</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issues</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira issues</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence pages</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The Knowledge capability solves this by introducing a generalized reposi=
tory knowledge layer:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>users manually add supported external records by URL</p></li>
<li>
<p>those records are normalized into stable <code>knowledge_items</code></p=
></li>
<li>
<p>their fetched content is stored as immutable document versions</p></li>
<li>
<p>explicit associations can be created to commits, checkpoints, artefacts,=
 or other knowledge items</p></li>
<li>
<p>future automations can later reuse the same low-level substrate</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Currentimplementationsnapshot">Cur=
rent implementation snapshot</h3>
<p>Implemented today:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>manual URL ingestion through <code>bitloops devql knowledge add</code></=
p></li>
<li>
<p>optional commit association at add time with <code>--commit</code></p></=
li>
<li>
<p>manual post-ingestion association through <code>bitloops devql knowledge=
 associate</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>manual refresh through <code>bitloops devql knowledge refresh</code></p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>version inspection through <code>bitloops devql knowledge versions</code=
></p></li>
<li>
<p>repository inventory listing through the <code>knowledge()</code> DevQL =
stage</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issue ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub PR ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira issue ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence page ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>shared Atlassian config</p></li>
<li>
<p>blob + DuckDB + relational storage split</p></li>
<li>
<p>version-aware source refs</p></li>
<li>
<p>version-aware knowledge targets</p></li>
<li>
<p>latest-target-version persistence for unversioned knowledge targets</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>capability health checks for config, storage, and connectors</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Planned but not yet implemented:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>structured child ingestion where the user explicitly requests hierarchy =
expansion</p></li>
<li>
<p>structured discussion enrichment for GitHub and Confluence sources while=
 preserving canonical root bodies</p></li>
<li>
<p>richer retrieval and traversal UX on top of the current repository inven=
tory stage</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>historicalIntent()</code> retrieval as a derived layer over commit=
-linked knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>broader relation semantics and current-state projections beyond current =
manual <code>associated_with</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>automation callers that reuse the same primitives for provider-resolved =
or scheduled flows</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Currentimplementationstatusagainst=
thisspecification">Current implementation status against this specification=
</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Area</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Status</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Notes</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge add</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Active via capability-host ingester <code>knowledge.add</code>.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge add --commit</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Internally runs ingest then commit association.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge associate</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Supports commit, knowledge, checkpoint, and artefact targets.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge refresh</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Re-fetches canonical source URL and creates a new version only when cont=
ent changed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge versions</code></p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Lists immutable versions for the resolved item.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p><code>knowledge()</code> stage</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Implemented, basic</p></td>
