<p>Not implemented as a stage yet.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Goals">Goals</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Support manual ingestion of external records by URL for the MVP provider=
s.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Make repository-scoped knowledge valid even without any semantic relatio=
n assertion.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Support optional manual commit association at add time as a CLI convenie=
nce.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Support explicit manual association after ingestion:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; knowledge item</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; commit</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; checkpoint</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; artefact</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Preserve immutable document versions using content-hash dedupe.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Preserve append-only, version-bound relation assertions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Preserve full provider payload fidelity.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Persist normalized/queryable metadata in DuckDB.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Use repo-local config under <code>knowledge.providers</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Support shared Atlassian config via <code>knowledge.providers.atlassian<=
/code>, with optional <code>jira</code> and <code>confluence</code> overrid=
es.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Establish the low-level ingestion and association primitives that later =
automations can call unchanged.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Successmetrics">Success metrics</h=
3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Manual ingestion of a supported URL creates or reuses exactly one <code>=
knowledge_item</code> for the canonical provider identity in the current re=
pository scope.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Re-ingesting the same canonical item with unchanged content creates zero=
 new document versions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Re-ingesting the same canonical item with changed content creates exactl=
y one new document version.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Manual ingestion without <code>--commit</code> results in a repository-s=
coped knowledge item with no relation assertion.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Manual ingestion with <code>--commit</code> creates a commit relation as=
sertion without changing repository-scoped validity.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Manual association is explicit, idempotent, and version-aware.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The full provider payload is preserved in blob storage.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Current and future discussion-heavy sources can be enriched later withou=
t losing the canonical root body.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Non-goals">Non-goals</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Automatic discovery during <code>bitloops devql ingest</code> in the ini=
tial MVP delivery</p></li>
<li>
<p>Natural-language explanation generation</p></li>
<li>
<p>Ranking or summarization of retrieved knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>Slack or other chat-platform ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Local filesystem file/folder ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Hosted multi-tenant permissions or access control</p></li>
<li>
<p>Cross-repo global deduplication of <code>knowledge_item</code> identity<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-4.Scope">4. Scope</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Inscopeforthefeaturefamily">In sco=
pe for the feature family</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Manual ingestion of supported external records by URL</p></li>
<li>
<p>Supported source types:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub issue</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub pull request</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira issue</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence page</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Repository-scoped knowledge items that exist without any semantic relati=
on assertion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Explicit manual associations after ingestion:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; knowledge item</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; commit</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; checkpoint</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item -&gt; artefact</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Optional <code>--commit &lt;sha_or_ref&gt;</code> convenience on manual =
add</p></li>
<li>
<p>Immutable document-version storage</p></li>
<li>
<p>Relation-assertion storage</p></li>
<li>
<p>Raw payload preservation plus normalized fields</p></li>
<li>
<p>Manual refresh of knowledge items</p></li>
<li>
<p>Version inspection of ingested knowledge items</p></li>
<li>
<p>Basic repository knowledge listing through <code>knowledge()</code></p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Future structured discussion enrichment for GitHub PRs, GitHub issues, a=
nd Confluence pages</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Currentlyimplementedinthecodebase"=
>Currently implemented in the codebase</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt; [--commit &lt;sha_or_ref&=
gt;]</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge associate &lt;source-ref&gt; --to &lt;tar=
get-ref&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge refresh &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;</code></p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql knowledge versions &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;</code></p>=
</li>
<li>
<p><code>repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")-&gt;knowledge()</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issue URL ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub PR URL ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira issue URL ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence page URL ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>Blob-backed full payload storage</p></li>
<li>
<p>DuckDB metadata storage</p></li>
<li>
<p>Relational source/item/relation persistence</p></li>
<li>
<p>Repo-local <code>knowledge.providers</code> config</p></li>
<li>
<p>Shared Atlassian config with Jira/Confluence overrides</p></li>
<li>
<p>Version-aware source refs</p></li>
<li>
<p>Version-aware target refs for knowledge targets</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Notyetimplemented">Not yet impleme=
nted</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>--include-children</code> or equivalent explicit hierarchy-expansi=
on option</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence child-page ingestion when explicitly requested</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub PR review/comment enrichment with structured review/comment secti=
ons</p></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issue comment and optional timeline enrichment</p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence footer/inline comment enrichment</p></li>
<li>
<p>richer graph traversal and retrieval surface on top of <code>knowledge()=
</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>current-state logical-edge projections over immutable relation assertion=
s</p></li>
<li>
<p>provider-resolved and automation-generated association flows reusing the=
 same substrate</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>historicalIntent()</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Outofscope">Out of scope</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Automation-first ingestion as part of the initial MVP delivery</p></li>
<li>
<p>full <code>historicalIntent()</code> retrieval</p></li>
<li>
<p>full polished retrieval UX beyond the low-level substrate</p></li>
<li>
<p>heuristic-only inferred relations as the only source of truth</p></li>
<li>
<p>cross-repo knowledge graph behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-5.Assumptions&amp;Constraints">5. =
Assumptions &amp; Constraints</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Knowledge must fit into the existing Bitloops/DevQL ecosystem, not becom=
e a disconnected side system.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Existing repository, commit, artefact, and checkpoint/session entities m=
ust be reused.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Repository scope is modeled on the knowledge item itself, not as a seman=
tic relation assertion.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Relation assertions are append-only and source-version-bound.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>ingest_source</code> is a pure materialization primitive.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>associate</code> is the primitive that creates semantic relations.=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>Config is repo-local and lives in <code>&lt;repo&gt;/.bitloops/config.js=
on</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Provider credentials live under <code>knowledge.providers</code>.</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>GitHub uses <code>knowledge.providers.github</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira and Confluence can share <code>knowledge.providers.atlassian</code>=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge.providers.jira</code> and <code>knowledge.providers.conf=
luence</code> are optional overrides over <code>knowledge.providers.atlassi=
an</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Blob storage is the source of full payload fidelity.</p></li>
<li>
<p>DuckDB stores document-version metadata and normalized/queryable fields =
rather than acting as the full raw payload store.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The relational store is the source of truth for identities and relation =
assertions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Discussion enrichment must not overwrite or flatten the canonical root b=
ody for discussion-heavy sources.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The active runtime path is the DevQL capability host and registered Know=
ledge pack, not dormant plugin code.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-6.UserStories">6. User Stories</h2=
>
<p><strong>US1 - Add repository-scoped knowledge</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to add a GitHub PR, GitHub issue, Jira issue, or Confluence page by =
URL <br>
So that it becomes part of my repository=E2=80=99s stored knowledge even if=
 I do not link it to a commit</p>
<p><strong>US2 - Add knowledge and immediately attach it to a commit</stron=
g> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to add a supported external record and associate it with a commit in=
 one CLI action <br>
So that I can quickly connect external context to a specific code change</p=
>
<p><strong>US3 - Explicitly connect existing knowledge to a commit</strong>=
 <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to associate an already-ingested knowledge item with a commit <br>
So that I can attach external rationale to code history after the knowledge=
 record already exists</p>
<p><strong>US4 - Explicitly connect one knowledge item to another</strong> =
<br>
As a developer <br>
I want to associate one ingested knowledge item with another ingested knowl=
edge item <br>
So that I can model relationships such as Confluence page -&gt; Jira issue =
explicitly</p>
<p><strong>US5 - Explicitly connect knowledge to a checkpoint</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to associate an ingested knowledge item with a checkpoint <br>
So that I can connect external context to Bitloops session history</p>
<p><strong>US6 - Explicitly connect knowledge to an artefact</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want to associate an ingested knowledge item with an artefact <br>
So that I can connect external context directly to a specific file, functio=
n, or module</p>
<p><strong>US7 - Preserve structure in hierarchical or discussion-heavy sou=
rces</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want GitHub PR reviews, GitHub issue discussion, and Confluence discussio=
n to preserve their structure rather than being flattened into one body <br=
>
So that later retrieval can distinguish authored content from later discuss=
ion</p>
<p><strong>US8 - Preserve history across document updates</strong> <br>
As a developer <br>
I want refreshed knowledge to create new immutable versions without rewriti=
ng old relations <br>
So that I can trust the historical record of what was linked at a given tim=
e</p>
<p><strong>US9 - Build the substrate for future automations</strong> <br>
As a Bitloops implementer <br>
I want manual flows to use low-level primitives that future automations can=
 reuse unchanged <br>
So that later hooks and provider-based automations do not require a data-mo=
del redesign</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-7.ConcreteUserScenarios">7. Concre=
te User Scenarios</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioA-AddaJiraissueasrepositor=
y-scopedknowledge">Scenario A - Add a Jira issue as repository-scoped knowl=
edge</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge add https://bitloops.a=
tlassian.net/browse/CLI-1370</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Bitloops fetches the Jira issue and normalizes it.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Bitloops stores one stable <code>knowledge_item</code> and one immutable=
 document version.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the Jira issue exists in repository knowledge scope</p></li>
<li>
<p>no commit relation is required</p></li>
<li>
<p>the issue is available for later manual association or retrieval</p></li=
>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioB-AddaConfluencepageandass=
ociateitwithaJiraissue">Scenario B - Add a Confluence page and associate it=
 with a Jira issue</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user adds a Confluence page by URL.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user adds a Jira issue by URL.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&l=
t;page_id&gt; --to knowledge:&lt;issue_id&gt;</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>both records exist as repository-scoped knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>the relation between them is stored explicitly</p></li>
<li>
<p>if the target version is omitted, the current latest target version is s=
tored at association time</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioC-AssociateanexistingJirai=
ssuetoacommitlater">Scenario C - Associate an existing Jira issue to a comm=
it later</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge add https://bitloops.a=
tlassian.net/browse/CLI-1370</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Later, the user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge associate knowl=
edge:&lt;issue_id&gt; --to commit:HEAD</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the Jira issue remains one repository-scoped knowledge item</p></li>
<li>
<p>a commit relation assertion is added later</p></li>
<li>
<p>the add flow and association flow remain separate</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioD-AddaConfluencepageandass=
ociateitwithanartefact">Scenario D - Add a Confluence page and associate it=
 with an artefact</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user adds a Confluence page by URL.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user identifies the relevant Bitloops artefact.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&l=
t;page_id&gt; --to artefact:&lt;artefact_id&gt;</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the Confluence page remains normal repository-scoped knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>the artefact relation assertion is stored explicitly</p></li>
<li>
<p>the external context can later be traversed directly from the artefact</=
p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioE-AddaGitHubPRandattachitt=
oacommit">Scenario E - Add a GitHub PR and attach it to a commit</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge add https://github.com=
/org/repo/pull/42 --commit HEAD</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Internally, Bitloops ingests the PR and then creates a commit associatio=
n.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the PR exists as a knowledge item</p></li>
<li>
<p>the commit relation assertion is stored explicitly</p></li>
<li>
<p>the stored payload remains the root PR payload only</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioF-RefreshaJiraissueafterit=
changes">Scenario F - Refresh a Jira issue after it changes</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user has already ingested a Jira issue.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The issue changes remotely.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge refresh knowledge:&lt;=
issue_id&gt;</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>if content changed, a new document version is created</p></li>
<li>
<p>old relation assertions remain attached to the old source version</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p>no historical links are rewritten</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioG-Inspectversionsforaknowl=
edgeitem">Scenario G - Inspect versions for a knowledge item</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user has already ingested a knowledge item multiple times.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql knowledge versions knowledge:&lt=
;item_id&gt;</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>immutable versions are listed</p></li>
<li>
<p>each version retains its own content hash and timestamps</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioH-Listrepositoryknowledgei=
nventorythroughDevQL">Scenario H - List repository knowledge inventory thro=
ugh DevQL</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user has already ingested multiple knowledge items.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The user runs: <br><code>bitloops devql query 'repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")=
-&gt;knowledge()-&gt;select(id,title,source_kind,provider)'</code></p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>one row is returned per repository knowledge item</p></li>
<li>
<p>each row uses the item's latest version metadata</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: implemented</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioI-EnrichaGitHubPRwithdiscu=
ssion">Scenario I - Enrich a GitHub PR with discussion</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user ingests a GitHub PR URL.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Bitloops preserves the PR root payload as the canonical root document.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>A later enrichment step fetches issue comments, reviews, and review comm=
ents.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the PR body remains distinct from review/discussion content</p></li>
<li>
<p>discussion is stored in structured sections rather than merged into <cod=
e>body_text</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval can later target body, comments, or reviews separately</p></li=
>
</ul>
<p>Status: planned</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-ScenarioJ-EnrichaGitHubissueorConf=
luencepagewithdiscussion">Scenario J - Enrich a GitHub issue or Confluence =
page with discussion</h3>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>The user ingests a GitHub issue or Confluence page.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Bitloops preserves the root body as the canonical root document.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>A later enrichment step fetches comments or inline discussions.</p></li>
</ol>
<p>Result:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the authored root content remains distinct from later commentary</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>discussion can be queried separately later</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Status: planned</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-8.FunctionalFlows">8. Functional F=
lows</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-8.1Manualaddandassociateflow">8.1 =
Manual add and associate flow</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">flowcha=
rt TD
    A["User runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt;`"] --&gt; B["Det=
ect provider and source kind"]
    B --&gt; C["Resolve provider config from `knowledge.providers`"]
    C --&gt; D["Fetch provider payload with configured credentials"]
    D --&gt; E["Normalize canonical identity and fields"]
    E --&gt; F["Create or reuse `knowledge_source`"]
    F --&gt; G["Create or reuse `knowledge_item` in repository scope"]
    G --&gt; H["Write full payload to blob storage"]
    H --&gt; I["Create new DuckDB document version only if content changed"=
]

    J["User runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate ...`"] --&gt; K["Resol=
ve source ref"]
    K --&gt; L["Resolve target ref"]
    L --&gt; M["Bind source to exact source document version"]
    M --&gt; N["Append immutable relation assertion"]</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-8.2Convenienceaddwithcommitassocia=
tion">8.2 Convenience add with commit association</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">sequenc=
eDiagram
    participant User
    participant CLI as bitloops devql knowledge add
    participant Service as Knowledge service
    participant Graph as Relational store
    participant Docs as DuckDB
    participant Blob as Blob store

    User-&gt;&gt;CLI: add &lt;url&gt; --commit &lt;sha_or_ref&gt;
    CLI-&gt;&gt;Service: ingest_source(url)
    Service-&gt;&gt;Graph: create/reuse source + item
    Service-&gt;&gt;Blob: persist full payload content
    Service-&gt;&gt;Docs: create version if content changed
    Service--&gt;&gt;CLI: knowledge_item_id + document_version_id
    CLI-&gt;&gt;Service: associate(knowledge:&lt;id&gt;, commit:&lt;sha&gt;=
, associated_with, manual_attachment)
    Service-&gt;&gt;Graph: append relation assertion
    Service--&gt;&gt;CLI: relation_assertion_id
    CLI--&gt;&gt;User: ingestion + association complete</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-8.3Version-preservingrefreshflow">=
8.3 Version-preserving refresh flow</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">sequenc=
eDiagram
    participant User
    participant CLI as bitloops devql knowledge refresh
    participant Service as Knowledge service
    participant Graph as Relational store
    participant Docs as DuckDB
    participant Blob as Blob store

    User-&gt;&gt;CLI: refresh knowledge:&lt;id&gt;
    CLI-&gt;&gt;Service: refresh_source(knowledge:&lt;id&gt;)
    Service-&gt;&gt;Service: resolve canonical source URL from existing ite=
m/source rows
    Service-&gt;&gt;Blob: persist new full payload if changed
    Service-&gt;&gt;Docs: compare new content hash with latest version
    alt content changed
        Service-&gt;&gt;Docs: append new document version
    else unchanged
        Service-&gt;&gt;Docs: reuse existing latest version
    end
    Note over Graph,Docs: Existing relation assertions remain unchanged and=
 continue to point to their original source versions.
    Service--&gt;&gt;CLI: refresh result</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-9.BDDScenarios">9. BDD Scenarios</=
h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-9.1Happypaths">9.1 Happy paths</h3=
>
<p><strong>S1 - Manual repository-scoped knowledge ingestion</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 supported external URL
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt;`
Then the system fetches the external record
And a repository-scoped knowledge item is created or reused by canonical id=
entity
And an immutable document version is stored or reused by content hash
And the full payload content is written to blob storage
And no semantic relation assertion is required</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S2 - Manual add with commit convenience</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 supported external URL
And a valid commit SHA in the current repository
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt; --commit &lt;s=
ha&gt;`
Then the system ingests the external record
And the system creates a commit relation assertion using `manual_attachment=
`
And the relation assertion references the exact source document version use=
d at add time</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S3 - Manual knowledge-to-commit association after ingestion</str=
ong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item has already been ingested
And a commit exists in the current repository
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&lt;id&gt;=
 --to commit:&lt;sha&gt;`
Then an immutable relation assertion is created
And the source side of the relation is bound to the exact source document v=
ersion used at call time</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S4 - Manual knowledge-to-knowledge association</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo knowledge items have already been ingested
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&lt;id1&gt=
; --to knowledge:&lt;id2&gt;`
Then an immutable relation assertion is created
And the source side of the relation is bound to the exact source document v=
ersion used at call time
And the target side records the current latest target version at associatio=
n time</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S5 - Versioned knowledge-to-knowledge association</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo knowledge items have already been ingested
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&lt;id1&gt=
;:&lt;version1&gt; --to knowledge:&lt;id2&gt;:&lt;version2&gt;`
Then an immutable relation assertion is created
And the exact source version is preserved
And the exact target version is recorded</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S6 - Manual knowledge-to-checkpoint association</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item has already been ingested
And a checkpoint exists
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&lt;id&gt;=
 --to checkpoint:&lt;checkpoint_id&gt;`
Then an immutable relation assertion is created
And the checkpoint becomes a valid query target for that knowledge item</pr=
e>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S7 - Manual knowledge-to-artefact association</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item has already been ingested
And an artefact exists
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge associate knowledge:&lt;id&gt;=
 --to artefact:&lt;artefact_id&gt;`
Then an immutable relation assertion is created
And the artefact becomes a valid query target for that knowledge item</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S8 - Re-ingest unchanged content</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item already exists for a canonical source identity
When the same source is ingested again with unchanged content
Then the same knowledge item is reused
And no new document version is created</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S9 - Re-ingest changed content</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item already exists for a canonical source identity
When the same source is ingested again with changed content
Then the same knowledge item is reused
And exactly one new document version is created
And the previous document versions remain unchanged</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S10 - Refresh preserves historical relations</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 knowledge item has at least one existing relation assertion
When the user refreshes the source and a new document version is created
Then existing relation assertions remain unchanged
And they continue to reference the original source document version
And no relation assertions are automatically rewritten to the new version</=
pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S11 - List repository knowledge through </strong><code>knowledge=
()</code></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 repository contains ingested knowledge items
When the user runs `repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")-&gt;knowledge()`
Then the stage returns one row per repository knowledge item
And each row uses the item's latest version metadata</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-9.2Discussionenrichmentcases">9.2 =
Discussion enrichment cases</h3>
<p><strong>S12 - GitHub PR discussion remains separate from the PR body</st=
rong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 GitHub pull request has been ingested
When discussion enrichment is added
Then the PR body remains the canonical root document
And issue comments, reviews, and review comments are stored as structured d=
iscussion data
And discussion content is not appended to top-level `body_text`</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S13 - GitHub issue discussion remains separate from the issue bo=
dy</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 GitHub issue has been ingested
When discussion enrichment is added
Then the issue body remains the canonical root document
And issue comments are stored separately from the root body
And timeline data remains optional and structured if added</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>S14 - Confluence comments remain separate from the page body</st=
rong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 Confluence page has been ingested
When discussion enrichment is added
Then the page body remains the canonical root document
And footer comments and inline comments are stored separately from the root=
 body
And comment content is not merged into top-level `body_text`</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-9.3Errorcases">9.3 Error cases</h3=
>
<p><strong>ERR1 - Unsupported or invalid URL</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 URL that does not match a supported provider/source type
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt;`
Then the command fails
And no knowledge item is created</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>ERR2 - Invalid commit association</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 supported external URL
And a commit SHA or ref that is invalid in the current repository
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt; --commit &lt;s=
ha_or_ref&gt;`
Then the command fails
And no commit relation assertion is created</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>ERR3 - Provider fetch failure during manual add</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given a=
 supported URL
And the provider fetch for that URL fails
When the user runs `bitloops devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt;`
Then the command fails for that item
And no partial knowledge item is persisted</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>ERR4 - Explicit version mismatch</strong></p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: text; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">Given t=
wo knowledge items exist
When the user uses a version id that does not belong to the selected knowle=
dge item
Then the association command fails
And no relation assertion is created</pre>
</div>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-10.AcceptanceCriteria">10. Accepta=
nce Criteria</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Currentimplementationcriteria">Cur=
rent implementation criteria</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Manual add without <code>--commit</code> creates or reuses a repository-=
scoped knowledge item and creates no relation assertion by default.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>Manual add with <code>--commit</code> creates a commit relation assertio=
n bound to the ingested source document version.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The supported current source types are GitHub pull requests, GitHub issu=
es, Jira issues, and Confluence pages.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Manual association works for knowledge -&gt; knowledge, knowledge -&gt; =
commit, knowledge -&gt; checkpoint, and knowledge -&gt; artefact.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Source refs support <code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;</code> and <code>kno=
wledge:&lt;item_id&gt;:&lt;version_id&gt;</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Knowledge targets support <code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;</code> and <co=
de>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;:&lt;version_id&gt;</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Unversioned knowledge targets resolve to the target item=E2=80=99s lates=
t version and persist that target version id.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Deprecated <code>knowledge_version:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> remains sup=
ported as a source-only compatibility syntax.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Refresh re-fetches the canonical source and preserves old relation asser=
tions against old source versions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Version inspection exposes immutable version history.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Re-ingesting unchanged content creates zero new document versions.</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>Re-ingesting changed content creates exactly one new document version.</=
p></li>
<li>
<p>Blob storage preserves the full source payload content.</p></li>
<li>
<p>DuckDB stores normalized/queryable document-version metadata.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The relational store stores source identity, knowledge item identity, an=
d relation assertions.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Atlassian credentials can be provided once via <code>knowledge.providers=
.atlassian</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira and Confluence can override the shared Atlassian config independent=
ly when needed.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge()</code> lists repository knowledge using latest version=
 metadata.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Unsupported URLs fail with a clear unsupported-source error.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Provider fetch failures do not leave partial persisted state.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Follow-upfeaturecriteria">Follow-u=
p feature criteria</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Discussion enrichment must preserve the canonical root document while st=
oring discussion in structured sections.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Optional child ingestion must remain explicit rather than silently broad=
ening ingest scope.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Retrieval should later support richer traversal and composition than tod=
ay=E2=80=99s repository inventory listing.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>historicalIntent()</code> should later retrieve commit-linked know=
ledge from the same underlying graph.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-11.CLIAndConfigContract">11. CLI A=
nd Config Contract</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-CurrentCLIcontract">Current CLI co=
ntract</h3>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge add &lt;url&gt; [--commit &lt;sha_or_ref&gt;]
bitloops devql knowledge associate &lt;source-ref&gt; --to &lt;target-ref&g=
t;
bitloops devql knowledge refresh &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;
bitloops devql knowledge versions &lt;knowledge-ref&gt;
bitloops devql query 'repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")-&gt;knowledge()'</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Associationrefsemantics">Associati=
on ref semantics</h3>
<p>Source refs:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;</code> -&gt; resolves to latest source v=
ersion</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> -&gt; uses exp=
licit source version</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_version:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> -&gt; deprecated sourc=
e compatibility syntax</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Target refs:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>commit:&lt;sha_or_ref&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;</code> -&gt; resolves to current latest =
target version</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> -&gt; uses exp=
licit target version</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>checkpoint:&lt;checkpoint_id&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>artefact:&lt;artefact_uuid&gt;</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Current behavior:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>source and target refs are both version-aware</p></li>
<li>
<p>if target version is omitted for a knowledge target, it is resolved to t=
he target item's latest version at association time</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_version:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> is not supported as a =
target ref</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Usermanualinteractionexamples">Use=
r manual interaction examples</h3>
<p>Prerequisites from repository root:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s init --agent codex
bitloops devql init</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Implementation note:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>bitloops devql init</code> is recommended for explicit local setup=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>Knowledge migrations are also applied lazily by the capability host on f=
irst ingester or stage use</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Add knowledge from URL:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge add "https://github.com/bitloops/bitloops/issues/42"</pre=
>
</div>
</div>
<p>Expected output includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge item: &lt;id&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge item version: &lt;version_id&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>status: ...</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Add a second knowledge item:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge add "https://bitloops.atlassian.net/browse/CLI-1370"</pre=
>
</div>
</div>
<p>List repository knowledge and recover ids:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql query 'repo("&lt;repo-name&gt;")-&gt;knowledge()-&gt;select(id,know=
ledge_item_version_id,title,source_kind,provider,updated_at)-&gt;limit(50)'=
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Associate source to commit:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;" --to "commit=
:HEAD"
bitloops devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;:&lt;so=
urce_version_id&gt;" --to "commit:HEAD"</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Associate source to knowledge target:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;" --to "knowle=
dge:&lt;target_item_id&gt;"
bitloops devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;" --to =
"knowledge:&lt;target_item_id&gt;:&lt;target_version_id&gt;"
bitloops devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;:&lt;so=
urce_version_id&gt;" --to "knowledge:&lt;target_item_id&gt;:&lt;target_vers=
ion_id&gt;"</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Associate to checkpoint and artefact:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;" --to "checkp=
oint:&lt;checkpoint_id&gt;"
bitloops devql knowledge associate "knowledge:&lt;source_item_id&gt;" --to =
"artefact:&lt;artefact_uuid&gt;"</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Inspect versions and refresh:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">bitloop=
s devql knowledge versions "knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;"
bitloops devql knowledge refresh "knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;"
bitloops devql knowledge versions "knowledge:&lt;item_id&gt;"</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Verify persisted relation rows directly:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: bash; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">sqlite3=
 .bitloops/stores/relational/relational.db \
'SELECT source_knowledge_item_version_id, target_type, target_id, target_kn=
owledge_item_version_id, relation_type, association_method, created_at
 FROM knowledge_relation_assertions
 ORDER BY created_at DESC
 LIMIT 20;'</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Repo-localconfigcontract">Repo-loc=
al config contract</h3>
<p>Provider credentials live in <code>&lt;repo&gt;/.bitloops/config.json</c=
ode> under <code>knowledge.providers</code>.</p>
<p>Recommended shape:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "knowledge": {
    "providers": {
      "github": {
        "token": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"
      },
      "atlassian": {
        "site_url": "https://bitloops.atlassian.net",
        "email": "${ATLASSIAN_EMAIL}",
        "token": "${ATLASSIAN_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>or</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">{
  "knowledge": {
    "providers": {
      "github": {
        "token": "${GITHUB_TOKEN}"
      },
      "jira": {
        "site_url": "https://bitloops.atlassian.net",
        "email": "${ATLASSIAN_EMAIL}",
        "token": "${ATLASSIAN_JIRA_TOKEN}"
      },
      "confluence": {
        "site_url": "https://bitloops.atlassian.net",
        "email": "${ATLASSIAN_EMAIL}",
        "token": "${ATLASSIAN_CONFLUENCE_TOKEN}"
      }
    }
  }
}</pre>
</div>
</div>
<p>Resolution rules:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub uses <code>knowledge.providers.github</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Jira uses <code>knowledge.providers.jira</code> if present, otherwise fa=
lls back to <code>knowledge.providers.atlassian</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence uses <code>knowledge.providers.confluence</code> if present, =
otherwise falls back to <code>knowledge.providers.atlassian</code></p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-12.StorageContract">12. Storage Co=
ntract</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Blobstore">Blob store</h3>
<p>Purpose:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>preserve the full provider payload and canonical body content at full fi=
delity</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples of current payload content:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub PR:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>body_text</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>raw_payload</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issue:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>body_text</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>raw_payload</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence page:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>body_html</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>body_text</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>raw_payload</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Current default local blob key:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge/&lt;repo_id&gt;/&lt;knowledge_item_id&gt;/&lt;knowledge_=
item_version_id&gt;/payload.json</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-DuckDB">DuckDB</h3>
<p>Purpose:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>store document-version metadata and normalized/queryable fields</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_item_id</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_item_version_id</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>provider</p></li>
<li>
<p>source kind</p></li>
<li>
<p>title</p></li>
<li>
<p>content hash</p></li>
<li>
<p>body preview</p></li>
<li>
<p>source timestamps</p></li>
<li>
<p>blob storage pointer</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Relationalstore">Relational store<=
/h3>
<p>Purpose:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>store source identity, repository-scoped knowledge identity, and relatio=
n assertions</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>knowledge source rows</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge item rows</p></li>
<li>
<p>commit relation assertions</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge-to-knowledge relations</p></li>
<li>
<p>checkpoint relations</p></li>
<li>
<p>artefact relations</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Implementation-aligned note:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>relation rows now include <code>target_knowledge_item_version_id</code><=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>compatibility migration adds this column when it is missing in older loc=
al SQLite databases</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-13.DataModelNotes">13. Data Model =
Notes</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Corepersistedconcepts">Core persis=
ted concepts</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_source</code></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>provider</p></li>
<li>
<p>source kind</p></li>
<li>
<p>canonical external identity</p></li>
<li>
<p>canonical URL</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_item</code></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>repository-scoped stable identity</p></li>
<li>
<p>source linkage</p></li>
<li>
<p>latest document version pointer</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>document version</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>immutable version metadata in DuckDB</p></li>
<li>
<p>full payload content in blob storage</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>relation assertion</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>source document version binding</p></li>
<li>
<p>target type and target id</p></li>
<li>
<p>optional target knowledge version id</p></li>
<li>
<p>provenance metadata</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Invariants">Invariants</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>repository-scoped knowledge is valid without commit linkage</p></li>
<li>
<p>canonical identity dedupes within the current repository scope</p></li>
<li>
<p>a new document version is created only when content hash changes</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>the full payload content is not lost when normalized fields evolve later=
</p></li>
<li>
<p>commit association is explicit and optional</p></li>
<li>
<p>future discussion enrichment must preserve authored root content separat=
ely from later discussion</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Implementation-aligneddecisionsnow=
reflectedinthespec">Implementation-aligned decisions now reflected in the s=
pec</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>The active implementation is capability-host based. The authoritative ru=
ntime path is <code>register_knowledge_pack(...)</code> plus the registered=
 Knowledge ingesters and stage.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge add --commit</code> is a convenience command over two pr=
imitives: ingest first, then associate to commit.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Source refs and knowledge targets are both version-aware in the active i=
mplementation.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Unversioned knowledge targets resolve to the target item=E2=80=99s lates=
t version and persist that exact target version id in the relation assertio=
n.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge_version:&lt;version_id&gt;</code> remains supported only=
 as deprecated source compatibility syntax. It is still rejected as a targe=
t.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Current manual relations use <code>relation_type =3D associated_with</co=
de> and <code>association_method =3D manual_attachment</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The current <code>knowledge()</code> stage is an inventory stage. It lis=
ts repository knowledge using latest version metadata and does not yet beha=
ve as a general graph-traversal stage.</p></li>
<li>
<p>The payload model already includes a <code>discussion</code> field for f=
uture structured enrichment, but current connectors populate <code>discussi=
on: None</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Deterministic ids are used for knowledge source, knowledge item, knowled=
ge item version, and relation assertion rows.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Persistence is rollback-safe across blob/document/relational writes to a=
void partial state on failure.</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-14.Provider-SpecificDiscussionEnri=
chment">14. Provider-Specific Discussion Enrichment</h2>
<p>The current MVP stores only the root document payload for each supported=
 source. That is sufficient for the current command contract, but it is not=
 the full long-term knowledge shape for discussion-heavy sources. The key d=
esign direction is to preserve a clear distinction between the canonical au=
thored root document and later discussion.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-14.1GitHubpullrequests">14.1 GitHu=
b pull requests</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>blob payload stores the root PR body and raw PR payload</p></li>
<li>
<p>the active connector does not yet enrich issue comments, reviews, or rev=
iew comments</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Recommendation:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>keep the PR body as the canonical root document</p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich the payload with structured discussion sections</p></li>
<li>
<p>do not append discussion directly into top-level <code>body_text</code><=
/p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-14.2GitHubissues">14.2 GitHub issu=
es</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>blob payload stores the root issue body and raw issue payload</p></li>
<li>
<p>the active connector does not yet enrich issue comments or timeline even=
ts</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Recommendation:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>keep the issue body as the canonical root document</p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich with structured issue comments, and possibly timeline data later<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>do not append comments or timeline entries into top-level <code>body_tex=
t</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-14.3Confluencepages">14.3 Confluen=
ce pages</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>blob payload stores the root page body as <code>body_html</code></p></li=
>
<li>
<p>extracted readable text is stored as <code>body_text</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>the active connector does not yet enrich footer or inline comments</p></=
li>
</ul>
<p>Recommendation:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>keep the page body as the canonical root document</p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich with structured footer comments and inline comments</p></li>
<li>
<p>do not merge comments into top-level <code>body_text</code></p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-14.4Cross-cuttingrecommendation">1=
4.4 Cross-cutting recommendation</h3>
<p>For all three source families:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>keep the current root payload behavior as the MVP baseline</p></li>
<li>
<p>treat comments and reviews as structured discussion enrichment</p></li>
<li>
<p>keep canonical authored content separate from later discussion</p></li>
<li>
<p>continue using blob storage as the full-fidelity source of truth</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>extract compact metadata into DuckDB later only when needed</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.FutureAdditionsandImprovements"=
>15. Future Additions and Improvements</h2>
<p>This section consolidates the future work that remains important after t=
he current implemented slice. The goal is to keep later implementation dire=
ction explicit instead of leaving it implied by scattered notes.</p>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.1Richerretrievalandtraversalont=
opofknowledge()">15.1 Richer retrieval and traversal on top of <code>knowle=
dge()</code></h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>knowledge()</code> is an inventory stage</p></li>
<li>
<p>it returns repository knowledge items using each item's latest version m=
etadata</p></li>
<li>
<p>it currently ignores <code>input_rows</code> and most stage composition =
context</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>evolve <code>knowledge()</code> from simple inventory listing into a ric=
her retrieval surface</p></li>
<li>
<p>support filtering and traversal by:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>provider</p></li>
<li>
<p>source kind</p></li>
<li>
<p>relation target type</p></li>
<li>
<p>relation type</p></li>
<li>
<p>exact version vs latest projection mode</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>support forward and reverse graph exploration such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>knowledge -&gt; commits</p></li>
<li>
<p>knowledge -&gt; artefacts</p></li>
<li>
<p>commit -&gt; linked knowledge</p></li>
<li>
<p>artefact -&gt; linked knowledge</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>make stage composition meaningful instead of replacing prior rows uncond=
itionally</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the current stage is enough for discovery, but not for graph-oriented us=
e cases</p></li>
<li>
<p>later DevQL users will need traversal, not just inventory</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval must remain explicit about whether it is showing exact histori=
cal assertions or current-state projections</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>retrieval arguments or companion stages for graph expansion</p></li>
<li>
<p>relation-aware row shapes</p></li>
<li>
<p>explicit version mode semantics</p></li>
<li>
<p>tests covering composition, traversal, and projection behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.2historicalIntent()asaderivedre=
trievallayer">15.2 <code>historicalIntent()</code> as a derived retrieval l=
ayer</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>historical intent is documented conceptually</p></li>
<li>
<p>it is not implemented as a stage or query surface</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>introduce <code>historicalIntent()</code> as a retrieval layer over the =
subset of knowledge linked to commits and, through them, to repository hist=
ory</p></li>
<li>
<p>allow historical-intent retrieval to start from commit, checkpoint, arte=
fact, or related repository context</p></li>
<li>
<p>preserve exact source-version traceability so explanations can be ground=
ed in the document version that was actually linked</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>historical intent is one of the main downstream reasons the Knowledge su=
bstrate exists</p></li>
<li>
<p>it should reuse the same graph rather than introduce a second storage mo=
del</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>a dedicated retrieval surface for historical-intent queries</p></li>
<li>
<p>ranking and explanation-assembly inputs built on knowledge relations</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>clear distinction between raw supporting assertions and higher-level exp=
lanation views</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.3Structureddiscussionenrichment=
fordiscussion-heavysources">15.3 Structured discussion enrichment for discu=
ssion-heavy sources</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the payload model already includes a <code>discussion</code> field</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>connectors currently populate <code>discussion: None</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>GitHub pull requests:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>issue_comments</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>reviews</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>review_comments</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>GitHub issues:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>issue_comments</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>optionally enrich with <code>timeline</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>Confluence pages:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>footer_comments</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>enrich with <code>inline_comments</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Design constraints:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>root authored content remains canonical</p></li>
<li>
<p>comments/reviews must not be flattened into top-level <code>body_text</c=
ode></p></li>
<li>
<p>enrichment should remain queryable as structured sections</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>for PRs and issues, much of the rationale lives in follow-up discussion<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p>for Confluence, page comments often contain caveats, objections, or late=
r clarifications</p></li>
<li>
<p>flattening discussion into the root body would create noisy content and =
confusing version churn</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>connector expansion for supported source families</p></li>
<li>
<p>structured payload population</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval that can distinguish root body from later discussion</p></li>
<li>
<p>versioning rules for discussion changes once the team decides what shoul=
d trigger a new document version</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.4Optionalchildingestionandhiera=
rchyexpansion">15.4 Optional child ingestion and hierarchy expansion</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>current ingest requests do not support explicit child expansion</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>add an explicit user-controlled child-ingestion mode such as <code>--inc=
lude-children</code> or equivalent</p></li>
<li>
<p>support hierarchy expansion only where it is semantically appropriate</p=
></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Confluence child pages when explicitly requested</p></li>
<li>
<p>future provider-specific hierarchical units where parent/child identity =
is meaningful</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Design constraints:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>hierarchy expansion must remain explicit rather than silently widening i=
ngestion scope</p></li>
<li>
<p>child items must preserve clear parent/child semantics if later modeled =
as relations such as <code>child_of</code></p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>some knowledge sources are hierarchical and users may want more than the=
 root document</p></li>
<li>
<p>automatic expansion would make ingestion less predictable and more expen=
sive</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>explicit CLI contract for child expansion</p></li>
<li>
<p>clear persistence and relation semantics for parent/child units</p></li>
<li>
<p>tests covering hierarchy ingestion and dedupe behavior</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.5Broaderrelationsemanticsandlog=
ical-edgeprojections">15.5 Broader relation semantics and logical-edge proj=
ections</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>manual relations use <code>associated_with</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>storage preserves append-only relation assertions</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>introduce additional relation semantics only when justified by retrieval=
 needs, such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>child_of</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>references</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>explains</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p>provide current-state logical-edge projections over immutable assertion =
history when useful</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>not every knowledge-to-knowledge link means the same thing</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval consumers may need both:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>exact historical assertion rows</p></li>
<li>
<p>a simpler current-state graph projection</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Design constraints:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>append-only assertion history remains the source of truth</p></li>
<li>
<p>projected current-state edges must be explicitly labeled as derived view=
s</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>richer relation vocabulary where there is a concrete consumer</p></li>
<li>
<p>projection rules for current-state edges</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval modes that separate raw assertions from derived graph views</p=
></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.6Automationandprovider-resolved=
associationflows">15.6 Automation and provider-resolved association flows</=
h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>current flows are manual CLI-driven</p></li>
<li>
<p>the substrate already separates ingestion and association primitives</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>add automation clients that reuse the same low-level primitives instead =
of writing directly to stores</p></li>
<li>
<p>support future association methods such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>provider_resolved</code></p></li>
<li>
<p><code>automation_generated</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Examples:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>commit -&gt; PR association via provider APIs</p></li>
<li>
<p>commit-message references to GitHub issues or Jira issues</p></li>
<li>
<p>PR body references to issues or tickets</p></li>
<li>
<p>scheduled refresh of tracked knowledge items</p></li>
<li>
<p>webhook-driven re-ingestion or linking</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the main architectural goal is to make automation a caller problem, not =
a data-model redesign problem</p></li>
<li>
<p>provenance must make it clear whether an edge came from manual action, p=
rovider-backed resolution, or automation</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>automation entry points reusing <code>ingest_source</code>, <code>associ=
ate</code>, <code>refresh_source</code>, and <code>list_versions</code></p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>richer provenance for automated associations</p></li>
<li>
<p>safeguards so automated flows remain debuggable and auditable</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.7ProviderandCLIergonomicsimprov=
ements">15.7 Provider and CLI ergonomics improvements</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>current ingestion is URL-based and explicit</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>add more ergonomic reference forms where ambiguity is manageable</p></li=
>
<li>
<p>improve diagnostics and setup experience</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Possible additions:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>provider-native refs such as <code>jira:PROJ-123</code></p></li>
<li>
<p>same-repo GitHub shorthand where repository context is clear</p></li>
<li>
<p>deeper connector/storage health checks beyond structural readiness</p></=
li>
<li>
<p>clearer CLI output for created vs reused items, versions, and associatio=
ns</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>the current explicit URL-first contract is safe, but not the most ergono=
mic long-term interface</p></li>
<li>
<p>setup and health diagnostics become more important as connectors and ret=
rieval get richer</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>carefully scoped shorthand forms</p></li>
<li>
<p>stronger health and configuration diagnostics</p></li>
<li>
<p>better operator-facing feedback in CLI results</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-15.8Testingandverificationexpansio=
n">15.8 Testing and verification expansion</h3>
<p>Current state:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>current BDD coverage is strong for the implemented manual slice</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Future improvement:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>extend tests to cover:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>discussion enrichment</p></li>
<li>
<p>child ingestion</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval traversal/projection semantics</p></li>
<li>
<p>automation provenance and method semantics</p></li>
<li>
<p>legacy-row behavior alongside newer target-version-aware associations</p=
></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p>Why this matters:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>future work will be more semantic and less trivial than the current inve=
ntory/add/associate slice</p></li>
<li>
<p>retrieval and automation changes are easier to mis-specify without execu=
table examples</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Expected future deliverables:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>new BDD scenarios for enrichment and retrieval</p></li>
<li>
<p>unit coverage for projection logic and automation provenance</p></li>
<li>
<p>targeted regression tests for compatibility with historical rows</p></li=
>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-16.OpenQuestions">16. Open Questio=
ns</h2>
