<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Discussionenrichmentquestions">Dis=
cussion enrichment questions</h3>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>ID</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Decision topic</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Context</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p>Current leaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E1</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What is the canonical root document for GitHub PRs?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>PR bodies and later reviews/comments should not be conflated.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Root PR body stays canonical; discussion is enrichment.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What should create a new document version when discussion enrichment exi=
sts?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Body edits, new comments, reviews, and state changes may churn versions =
differently.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Keep unresolved for later design.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E3</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Should enriched discussion be stored as structured arrays or separate ch=
ild knowledge items?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Structured arrays are simpler; child items are more flexible.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Structured arrays first, child-item model later if needed.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E4</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Should GitHub issue enrichment include timeline as well as comments?</p>=
</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Timeline adds lifecycle context but may create extra churn.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Comments first; timeline remains optional.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E5</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Should Confluence comments and child pages be modeled the same way?</p><=
/td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Page hierarchy and comments are different relationships.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>No; treat them as different concepts.</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>E6</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>What retrieval modes should future enrichment support?</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Consumers may want only authored body, only objections, only final resol=
ution, or only inline comments.</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p>Preserve structure now so retrieval can stay selective later.</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-17.TestPlan">17. Test Plan</h2>
<h3 id=3D"Knowledge-FeatureSpecification-Unittests">Unit tests</h3>
<ul>
<li>
